## Final acceptance criteria

- ☐ DwarfUI packages the tooltip system without a SoulSearch runtime
  dependency.
- ☐ Busted is installed and run through LuaRocks using the repository test
  tooling.
- ☐ Any compatible DFHack widget can declare static tooltip text without a
  tooltip-specific subclass.
- ☐ A terminal control can dynamically replace or clear its tooltip and the
  renderer observes the change on the next update.
- ☐ Pointer targeting is generic, clipping-aware, modal-aware, and independent
  of tooltip text.
- ☐ Tooltip lookup never invokes a provider or falls back to an ancestor.
- ☐ The renderer never becomes its own pointer target.
- ☐ Normal screens and overlays maintain isolated agents, targets, text, and
  lifecycle state.
- ☐ Mouse-out, widget removal, host teardown, and reload do not leave stale
  visible text or retained pointer targets.
- ☐ Local Busted/build/package checks pass and are reported separately from
  live DFHack screen/overlay proof.
- ☐ The registration-only API has been evaluated only after parity completion,
  and the accepted design is backed by lifecycle evidence.
- ☐ The final downstream integration contract requires no manual lifecycle work
  beyond what the Phase 8/9 evidence found unavoidable.
